      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING CRUELLA (3) tends to drift back and work into the race, winding up late into second (29.69) in a Grade 5 at Nowra last time and making it four straight placings. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Rates highly and will give a great sight. VINTAGE GLOW (2) turned spotting a big start finishing fifth (22.79) last time in a Grade 5 at Bulli. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. CASH ME OUT (5) missed the frame latest when sixth at Gosford (30.59) but scored four back at this track (29.97). Has never been out of the money in three starts this course and distance. Deserves plenty of respect. DRINK TO THAT (1) racing over this distance brings the best out in him.",
